The paper deals with graph partitioning and spectral algorithms, which are common topics in computer science. The use of eigenvalues and conductance measures suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. The mention of low-conductance sets and high conductance induced subgraphs also suggests a connection to machine learning and clustering, which could place the paper in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of spectral algorithms and the focus on eigenvalues could also suggest a connection to information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
